3. Aozora Bunko annotation specification snapshots (fair use / quotation)
================================================================================

HTML snapshots of the Aozora Bunko (青空文庫) annotation specification
are reproduced under docs/specs/aozora/ verbatim for offline technical
reference during afm development. The material is (c) Aozora Bunko
volunteers and remains their property; afm includes the snapshots under a
limited fair-use / quotation exception grounded in the fact that the text
is short, stable, and central to an interoperability effort.

See docs/specs/aozora/README.md for the full list of upstream URLs, the
snapshot date, and the rights-holder removal policy: if a rights-holder
requests removal, the files will be dropped and offline access will fall
back to `WebFetch` against the live site.


================================================================================
4. Aozora Bunko sample works (public domain)
================================================================================

Sample works under spec/aozora/fixtures/ are sourced from Aozora Bunko
(https://www.aozora.gr.jp/). Aozora Bunko distributes works whose
copyrights have expired under Japanese law, making them public domain in
Japan. Each fixture directory carries its own README naming the author,
translator (if any), and the relevant public-domain rationale.

The flagship fixture spec/aozora/fixtures/56656/ is Fyodor M. Dostoyevsky's
『罪と罰』 (Crime and Punishment) in the Japanese translation by 米川正夫
(Masao Yonekawa). Aozora Bunko card number 56656
(https://www.aozora.gr.jp/cards/001485/card56656.html). Public domain: the
author died in 1881 and the translator in 1966; the Japanese translation
copyright has lapsed under Japanese law.


